 9. the person who growsdahlia is on the far left##1
10. the person playing whist is between the person traveling to new-york and the person who's sport is weightlifting##2
11. the person who likes lavender is on the right of the person who's sport is ice-hockey##1
12. the person playing backgammon is on the right of the person who growsamaryllis##1
13. the person who's sport is baseball is on the left or right of the person who growsaconite##3
14. the person playing whist is in an odd position##4

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1      |     2      |     3      |    4     |
| Sport         | ice-hockey | volleyball  | baseball | weightlifting  |
| City   | marseilles     | new-york    | liverpool     | prague      |
| Color   | black  | lavender  | ebony     | chestnut |
| Flower           | dahlia      | begonia | amaryllis       | aconite     |
| Game     | scrabble      | chess | whist  | backgammon   |

